#: index.docbook:23
msgid	"Date and Time"
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:25
msgid	"You can use this module to alter the system date and time, using a "
	"convienent graphical interface."
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:28
msgid	"You must have system administrator (<systemitem "
	"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>) access to change the system "
	"date and time. If you do not have this access level, this module "
	"will only show you the current settings."
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:33
msgid	"When you first start, you are in display mode only. To modify your "
	"settings, click on <guibutton>Modify</guibutton>. If you are logged "
	"in as root, you will go straight to the change dialog. If not, KDE "
	"will ask for a superuser password."
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:39
msgid	"Modifying your settings"
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:41
msgid	"You set the date using the left half of the module. Simply choose "
	"your month (the drop down box at the top), year (the spin box at the "
	"top), and the day of the month (simply click on the day in the "
	"calendar)."
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:45
msgid	"You set the time using the spin box at the bottom of the clock. "
	"Simply click in the hour, minutes or seconds box. You can directly "
	"enter your value, or you can click on the <guiicon>+</guiicon> or "
	"<guiicon>-</guiicon> buttons to adjust that value up one value."
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:50
msgid	"The time is represented in 24 hour format. If you want the system "
	"time to be set to 8:00 PM, you need to set the hour spinbox to "
	"<guilabel>20</guilabel> (8 + 12). If you want the system time set to "
	"8:00 AM, you should set the hour spinbox to <guilabel>8</guilabel>."
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:55
msgid	"You can then click on the <guilabel>Time Zone</guilabel> tab."
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:56
msgid	"Simply select your new timezone from the drop down box in the middle "
	"of the screen"
msgstr	""

#: index.docbook:59
msgid	"When you have set the correct date and time, simply click "
	"<guibutton>Apply</guibutton> to make the changes permanent."
msgstr	""

